 START--><a href="http://www.eqknights.com/goals/goals_main.htm">Goals</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, our <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqknights.com/our_code/code.htm">Code</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, and our <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqknights.com/policy/policy.html">Policy</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. Once you understand them and agree to follow these paths, you'll need to get to know a few members. <br>
Below is our current policy regarding joining the Knights of Freedom:<br>
<br>
APPLICATION/ INVITE POLICY<br>
<br>
All prospective members (including alternates) must complete the Online Application via the Web Site.<br>
<br>
All applicants, including alternates, must be unguilded at the time of application and remain so throughout the application process.<br>
<br>
Applications from main characters will be posted in our GATE HOUSE forum for 1 week. If there are no objections during that week, the character will be invited as a Squire on a probationary term. Once invited, the character must secure 3 sponsors within 1 month - if they do not have the 3 sponsors in 1 month, or there are objections raised during this time, they will be removed from the guild. Squires must remain Anonymous when possible. When 3 sponsors are obtained, the character is invited to the guild and may remove their Anonymous flag, but remains on probation until they have attended 3 KoF raids or other events and 1 additional month has passed. After this month, the character will be evaluated for how well they fit with the guild, and a final determination made regarding their guild status.<br>
<br>
Squires and Knights on probation may not apply for alternate characters to be invited to the guild.<br>
<br>
Sponsors: Any member of the guild other than Squires and Knights on probation may sponsor recruits. Members are not limited to how many recruits they may sponsor. Sponsors must let the Steward of the Order or another officer know about their sponsorship, which will then be posted under the recruit's application in the SQUIRE'S BARRACKS forum.<br>
<br>
Minimum level for invite: <br>
For New Applicants: Minimum of level 40.<br>
<br>
For Alternate Characters of Existing Members: Alternate Characters must be a minimum of level 20. Alternate Characters may not apply if the member's main character or any of their other guilded alternate characters are currently below level 40.<br>
<br>
&quot;Real Life&quot; immediate family members of an existing Knight of Freedom may apply at minimum level of 10 (this exception is to promote family unity<br>
